{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4390c434-b2d9-4a7b-991f-25b2dea9e59f","content":"With MTP (Microsoft.Testing.Platform) enabled via `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner`, the VSTest `--filter` syntax no longer applies. MTP uses **`--treenode-filter`** with a path-based expression.\n\n**Your old filter:**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Translated for MTP:**\n```\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n| VSTest | MTP (`--treenode-filter`) |\n|--------|--------------------------|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` | `/*X*` (glob on the node path) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (property filter in brackets) |\n| `&` (AND) | Combine in same expression or use `&` |\n| `--filter` | `-- --treenode-filter` (args after `--` pass to MTP) |\n\nThe `/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]` matches any test node whose path contains \"IntegrationTests\" **and** has the trait `Category=Smoke`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f36d0853-7f9c-4d02-b956-9a79bc558bed","outputTokens":298,"requestId":"E3D6:14EAB3:16A2F38:1948C6E:6A05211A"},"id":"434a182f-7d9b-4e81-9775-0309d24fc167","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:10:58.056Z","parentId":"ffb4dc15-5fe0-4507-83bf-6fab687bcc8e"}
